Trinity High School, Oguta, Old Boys Association (TOBA) will mark its 2022 national reunion with a book launch on June 12. Events will kick off with Trinity Sunday service at Assumpta Cathedral, Owerri, at 9:30am, and a reception at Art Nouveau Centre, Owerri, at noon. The book: Trinity High School Oguta – Reminiscenes recounts past events of the school.   Akiolu wins House of Reps APC primaries     ‘Unite and give APC victory in 2023’     Challenges, solutions to African tech growth    Association’s President Godwin Achunine said  there will be a lecture, gala night/fellowship and fund-raising. He said: “Trinity Sunday is a special day for solemn and reverential worship of the Blessed Trinity – God the Father,  Son and Holy Spirit. This day was a special day for students at Trinity. “On each Blessed Trinity Sunday day, our Proprietor Chief HPO Udom (Papa or Prop) kills a cow and entertain students…”